<<Iraq is a seriously messed up country. I didn't trust Saddam Hussein back
at the time. I'm sure he kept a lot of weapons and did not destroy them like
he told, but who knows where they are now. (Syria? Iran?) Obviously,
attacking Iraq had little relevance to the War on Terrorism. Iraq has
supported very little terrorist activity after the first Gulf War, and not
too much beforehand. The Iraqi's regime was not a threat as an advocate of
